331
00:25:34,640 --> 00:25:35,740
We're planning to sell them

332
00:25:35,740 --> 00:25:37,320
and earn some money to have a good meal.

333
00:25:38,340 --> 00:25:39,820
I'm almost done putting them away too.

334
00:25:40,260 --> 00:25:41,340
These are workbooks.

335
00:25:41,470 --> 00:25:42,740
Those are books and papers.

336
00:25:42,870 --> 00:25:43,670
Sell them all.

337
00:25:45,840 --> 00:25:48,280
You kept those from
primary school and junior middle school?

338
00:25:48,340 --> 00:25:49,420
You didn't look like

339
00:25:49,420 --> 00:25:50,260
the nostalgic type.

340
00:25:52,580 --> 00:25:54,430
This is precious to me. Don't touch it.

341
00:25:55,020 --> 00:25:55,870
It's precious?

342
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:57,670
I'd like to see
what's so precious about it.

343
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,020
Jing Xichi, give it back to me.

344
00:25:59,230 --> 00:26:00,520
Isn't it just an English book?

345
00:26:00,780 --> 00:26:01,390
What's this?

346
00:26:04,020 --> 00:26:04,780
Is this you?

347
00:26:05,430 --> 00:26:05,990
Yeah.

348
00:26:08,820 --> 00:26:11,470
I didn't know you were quite cute
when you were little.

349
00:26:11,540 --> 00:26:12,910
What do you mean by that?

350
00:26:12,950 --> 00:26:14,230
Am I not cute now?

351
00:26:14,390 --> 00:26:15,470
You're a weirdo now.

352
00:26:15,680 --> 00:26:17,660
You're the weirdest
in the whole compound.

353
00:26:17,870 --> 00:26:18,820
Besides me and Song,

354
00:26:18,820 --> 00:26:20,120
no one dares to sit next to you.

355
00:26:20,120 --> 00:26:21,820
Who are you calling a weirdo?
Give it back.

356
00:26:21,840 --> 00:26:23,020
I used to be popular. Alright?

357
00:26:24,260 --> 00:26:25,150
You don't behave

358
00:26:25,230 --> 00:26:26,190
